controllers follow the shared resolution and
delete sequences with imported waits and
controller-local policy.
service: vbsinst
slug: vbsinstance
kind: VbsInstance
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
follow-up: create=GetWorkRequest ->
GetVbsInstance; update=GetWorkRequest ->
GetVbsInstance; delete=GetWorkRequest ->
GetVbsInstance/ListVbsInstances confirm-delete
supported drift: definedTags, displayName,
freeformTags, isResourceUsageAgreementGranted
(+1 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId, name
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_vbs_inst_vbs_instances filters
compartmentId, name, id; exact compartmentId
plus name unique match in ACTIVE, CREATING, or
UPDATING; duplicate matches fail
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE as
success, and DELETING as terminating; FAILED is
terminal and DELETED is only a
delete-confirmation target.
Create, update, and delete responses expose
work-request headers but do not return a
VbsInstance body. The runtime resumes through
GetWorkRequest, recovers the affected
VbsInstance OCID from work-request resources,
and then rereads GetVbsInstance before settling.
Pre-create reuse only runs when
spec.compartmentId and spec.name are present and
keeps exact compartmentId plus name matching
bounded to ACTIVE, CREATING, or UPDATING
summaries.
Only displayName,
isResourceUsageAgreementGranted,
resourceCompartmentId, freeformTags, and
definedTags reconcile in place; name remains
create-time identity and
ChangeVbsInstanceCompartment stays out of scope
for the published runtime.
The provider-only idcs_access_token header input
is intentionally not part of the published CRD
surface for VbsInstance.
Required status projection keeps VbsAccessUrl,
lifecycleDetails, and systemTags on the
published kind, and the runtime has no secret
side effects.
end note
